<subSubSection type="nomenclature">
<paragraph pageNumber="1">
[[ Genus 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:085BCF8E-AF07-4A2A-933E-A8FFA5CE820C" class="Actinopterygii" family="Erethistidae" genus="Erethistoides" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Erethistoides Hora 1950:190" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="1" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Erethistoides</taxonomicName>
]]
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection type="discussion">
<paragraph pageNumber="1">
Members of the genus 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:085BCF8E-AF07-4A2A-933E-A8FFA5CE820C" class="Actinopterygii" family="Erethistidae" genus="Erethistoides" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Erethistoides Hora 1950:190" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="1" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Erethistoides</taxonomicName>
are small erethistid catfishes traditionally diagnosed by a strongly depressed head and body and the presence of diverging serrations (antrorse on the distal half and retrorse on the proximal half) on the anterior edge of the pectoral spine. The genus, known from the sub-Himalayan region of the Indian subcontinent, currently includes two nominal species: 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:F07A5213-8D5F-40C8-ACB7-2CB6B1268D20" class="Actinopterygii" family="Erethistidae" genus="Erethistoides" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Erethistoides montana Hora 1950:191" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="1" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="montana">E. montana Hora</taxonomicName>
, 1950 and 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:A4956CC4-3569-46C7-BE2E-37885905CA2D" class="Actinopterygii" family="Erethistidae" genus="Erethistoides" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Erethistoides montana pipri Hora 1950:193" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="1" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="pipri">E. pipri (Hora</taxonomicName>
, 1950).
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageNumber="1">
During a recent ichthyological survey of the northern Bengal region in India, specimens of 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:085BCF8E-AF07-4A2A-933E-A8FFA5CE820C" class="Actinopterygii" family="Erethistidae" genus="Erethistoides" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Erethistoides Hora 1950:190" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="1" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Erethistoides</taxonomicName>
were obtained, which upon further study, proved to be an undescribed species. The species is described here as 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:439BE4CD-38E1-4064-967E-FD6A36F79871" class="Actinopterygii" family="Erethistidae" genus="Erethistoides" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Erethistoides sicula Ng 2005" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="1" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="sicula">Erethistoides sicula</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicNameLabel rank="species">new species</taxonomicNameLabel>
. It was also found that the traditional diagnosis of 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:085BCF8E-AF07-4A2A-933E-A8FFA5CE820C" class="Actinopterygii" family="Erethistidae" genus="Erethistoides" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Erethistoides Hora 1950:190" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="1" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Erethistoides</taxonomicName>
is inadequate due to variation in the morphology of the pectoral-spine serrations. Here, four new synapomorphies diagnosing 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:085BCF8E-AF07-4A2A-933E-A8FFA5CE820C" class="Actinopterygii" family="Erethistidae" genus="Erethistoides" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Erethistoides Hora 1950:190" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="1" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Erethistoides</taxonomicName>
are identified and briefly discussed.
</paragraph>
